    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Late-19th-century ingrain carpets which were woven in one piece, with border and fringe. They could be used as crumbcloths, and were easy to move and clean.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
